    'legal.privacy.section1.2.content': 'We process your personal data on this basis only after your explicit, unambiguous, and voluntary consent. There will be no adverse consequences if you refuse data processing.\nConsent constitutes a separate legal basis for processing, with the purpose specified in it and distinct from purposes listed in this policy. If you provide consent, until you withdraw it or terminate any contractual relationship with us, we may prepare appropriate product/service offers tailored for you by analyzing your core personal data.\nData processed on this basis:\nPersonal data used for direct marketing purposes, including website usage data and social media profile data.\nDisclosure to Third Parties:\nWe may share your data with marketing agencies, Facebook, Google, or similar entities on this basis.\n\nWithdrawal of Consent\nConsents given may be withdrawn at any time without affecting contract performance. If you withdraw consent for any or all processing purposes above, we will cease using your personal data for those purposes. Withdrawal does not affect the lawfulness of processing based on consent prior to withdrawal. To withdraw consent, simply use our website or contact us.\nData collected under this basis will be deleted upon your request or 12 months after initial collection.',
