    'legal.privacy.section3.deletion': 'Users may request deletion if one or more of the following apply:\n- Personal data is no longer necessary for the collection purpose;\n- Consent is withdrawn and no other legal basis for processing exists;\n- User objects to processing and no overriding legal grounds exist;\n- Personal data was unlawfully processed;\n- Deletion is necessary to comply with legal obligations under EU or national laws;\n- Accuracy of personal data is contested (in which case, processing is restricted while verified);\n- Processing is unlawful and the user prefers restriction over deletion;\n- Data is no longer needed for processing purposes but requested for legal claims;\n- User objects pending verification regarding lawful basis priority.',
    'legal.privacy.section3.restriction': 'Users may restrict processing when:\n- Contesting accuracy, with restriction during verification;\n- Processing is unlawful but refusal to delete;\n- Data not needed for processing but required for claims;\n- Objection pending verification of lawful basis dominance.',
    'legal.privacy.section3.1.title': '3.1 Right to Object Regarding Contract Performance',
